  "page_number": 19,
  "context": "19 A full-time faculty may be allowed a maximum teaching load of 30 contact hours per week. However, a faculty member with a documented Very Satisfactory teaching performance may be allowed to handle additional six (6) hours per week (CHED-MARINA Memorandum Circular No. 01, series of 2022).\n\nSection 36 The computation oh honorarium based on the Prime Hourly Teaching Rate (PHTR) for teaching overload in the undergraduate program shall conform with Chapter 7, Section 7.13 of the DBM Circular Letter No. 2007-6 (Manual on Position Compensation and Classification).\n\nSection 37 The computation for overtime pay of the teaching overload on a scheduled workday and on a rest day or scheduled day off, holiday, or special non-working day shall use the formula as stipulated in the Joint Circular No. 02, s.2015 dated November 25, 2015 of the Civil Service Commission and the Department of Budget and Management.\n\nSection 38 Administrative personnel, regardless of employment status, who wish to teach in the undergraduate program outside of the 8-hour work period shall be compensated on a fixed hourly rate based on the highest educational attainment and the expertise of the course(s) taught Board Resolution No. 17-2005, Board pursuant to Resolution No. 44-205, Board Resolution No. 55- and 2016. The hourly rate as embodied in the aforementioned resolutions shall be subject to change should there be amendments in the succeeding year(s).\n\nVII. Midyear Classes\n\nSection 1 Faculty members assigned/requested to teach course(s) in the undergraduate program during midyear break shall be allowed to handle a maximum of 2 courses/preparations or 9 teaching units.\n\nSection 2 The compensation of honorarium based on the Prime Hourly Teaching Rate (PHTR) for teaching overload in the undergraduate program shall conform with Chapter 7, Section 7.13 of the DBM Circular Letter No. 2007-6 (Manual on Position Compensation)",
